# API layer architecture

Every API integration follows the same three-layer split. The Infloww
integration is the canonical example — mirror its shape for any new domain.

## Layer flow

```
Component / Page
      ↓
<domain>.hooks.ts          ← React Query wrappers only
      ↓
<domain>.service.ts        ← class with one method per endpoint
      ↓
api.ts                     ← single shared axios instance (origin only)
```

## Layer responsibilities

1. **`<domain>.hooks.ts`** — thin React Query wrappers (`useQuery`,
   `useMutation`). Owns `queryKey`, `staleTime`, `enabled`. Contains no
   fetch/axios calls. Calls methods on the singleton service instance.

2. **`<domain>.service.ts`** — a **class** with one method per endpoint.
   Exports a singleton instance (`export const xService = new XService()`).
   Defines a `private static readonly BASE_PATH` constant for its sub-path
   (e.g. `"/api/infloww"`). Knows nothing about React or React Query.

3. **`api.ts`** — a single axios instance whose `baseURL` is the **origin
   only** (e.g. `http://localhost:3000` in dev, the deployed origin in prod).
   Each service class composes the full URL as `BASE_PATH + endpoint`.
   Owns the response interceptor that maps non-2xx into `ApiError`.

## URL composition

```
axios baseURL          service BASE_PATH    endpoint
http://localhost:3000  +  /api/infloww   +  /creators
                       ↑ defined in          ↑ passed to api.get()
                         service class
```

## Naming and location

For a domain `X`, colocate `x.hooks.ts` and `x.service.ts` under
`src/lib/<domain>/`. Keep the shared `api.ts` at `src/lib/<domain>/api.ts`
(or `src/lib/api.ts` if shared across domains).

## Example skeleton

```typescript
// x.service.ts
class XService {
  private static readonly BASE_PATH = "/api/x";

  private url(endpoint: string) {
    return `${XService.BASE_PATH}${endpoint}`;
  }

  async getItems(params: GetItemsParams): Promise<ItemsResponse> {
    const { data } = await api.get(this.url("/items"), { params });
    return data;
  }
}

export const xService = new XService();

// x.hooks.ts
export function useItems(opts: UseItemsOptions) {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ["x", "items", opts],
    queryFn: () => xService.getItems(opts),
  });
}
```
